## Looking for Another Target

i first think about overwriting the return address, but this is not possible because there is no buffer overflow.

the only thing i control is the format string passed to `printf()`.

i continue reading the disassembly and notice that before the program terminates it executes:

```asm
call 0x80483d0 <exit@plt>
```

if i can redirect this call somewhere else, i gain control.

so instead of overwriting a return address, i decide to overwrite the GOT entry of `exit()` and replace it with the address of `o()`.

then when the program executes:

```c
exit();
